{"id": 243276046, "title": "Our national teams remain a priority in our programs.", "text": "Sheikh Hamdan bin Mubarak Al Nahyan, President of the Emirates Football Association, called for doubling the work, giving and initiatives that would create an environment that stimulates achievements, noting that the 2023-2024 season was distinguished by the Al Ain team winning the AFC Champions League title for the second time in its history. . Sheikh Hamdan bin Mubarak Al Nahyan extended his sincere thanks to the wise leadership for its continued interest in sports activity in all its specialties. This came during the Ordinary General Assembly Meeting No. 1 of 2024, yesterday, via video communication technology. The President of the Federation added that the \u201cGeneral Assembly\u201d has great responsibilities, because the ambitions of Emirati football are growing every day, and that these aspirations require facing challenges with sound planning, precise implementation, and continuing work without stopping. He stressed that forming judicial and legal committees and reviewing all the details of the new season is necessary to preserve the gains achieved in previous seasons and improve work in the coming seasons. The Federation President said: \u201cOur national teams remain a priority in our programs, and we will remain keen to provide them with all the reasons for success, especially the first national team, which is awaiting important participation in the qualifiers for the 2026 World Cup finals. We are also making a great effort to develop our local competitions technically and organizationally.\u201d \u201cAs well as developing the administrative and legal aspects, the arbitration corps, women\u2019s and beach football, and every field that serves the general goal.\u201d During the meeting, proposals to amend the bylaws were approved, as well as proposals to amend the regulations governing the implementation of the bylaws. The judicial committees and arbitration bodies of the Football Association were also approved for the new season, as the Disciplinary Committee included Saeed Al-Houti (Chairman), Hamda Al-Shamsi (Deputy), and members Hassan Al-Shaibani, Salman Al-Tawil and Badr Khamis. The Players\u2019 Status and Transfers Committee included Aisha Al-Taniji (Chairman), Abdullah Al-Ghailani (Deputy), and members Rashid Qassim, Abdullah Al-Rukn and Rashid Bin Suwaidan. The Dispute Resolution Chamber included Ali Al-Haddad (Chairman), Hamid Darwish (Deputy), and members Hamad Al-Ustadh, Tariq Al-Balouki, Jameel Al-Harthi, Ahmed Al-Shamsi, and Aisha Al-Dhahri. The Appeals Committee on the decisions of the Disciplinary Committee included Saleh Al-Hamrani (Chairman), Faisal Al-Haddad (Deputy), and members Arif Mahmoud, Ammar Al-Alili and Hussein Al-Hammadi, while the Appeals Committee on decisions on the status and transfers of players \u2013 the Dispute Resolution Chamber included Ahmed Suleiman (Chairman) and Ali Shams. (Deputy), and members Abdulaziz Al-Ablam, Shihab Ahmed, and Maitha Talib.", "summary": "<p>Sheikh Hamdan bin Mubarak Al Nahyan, President of the Emirates Football Association, called for doubling the work, giving and initiatives that would create an environment that stimulates achievements, noting that the 2023-2024 season was distinguished by the Al Ain team winning the AFC Champions League title for the second time in its history. . Sheikh [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://thenewsglory.com/our-national-teams-remain-a-priority-in-our-programs/\">Our national teams remain a priority in our programs.</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://thenewsglory.com\">The News Glory</a>.</p>", "url": "https://thenewsglory.com/our-national-teams-remain-a-priority-in-our-programs/", "image": "https://www.emaratalyoum.com/polopoly_fs/1.1864139.1719603761!/image/image.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-29 03:03:26", "author": "The News Glory", "authors": ["The News Glory"], "language": "en", "source_country": "in", "sentiment": 0.648}